article.headline: American 65, Navy 48
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP)-- Arvydas Eitutavicius scored 15 points, Andre Ingram added 12 and American never trailed in a 65-48 victory over Navy on Thursday night. American (6-7, 10-16 Patriot League) forced 20 Navy turnovers and outrebounded the Midshipmen 38-30 to win for the third time in four games. Greg Sprink and Carlton Baldwin scored 12 points each for Navy (10-16, 3-10), which has lost three straight. It was the Mids' second-lowest point total of the season. Ahead 28-19 at halftime, the Eagles put the game away by outscoring the Mids 30-14 to start second half. Eitutavicius scored nine of his points in that stretch and Ingram finished it off with leaner and a 3-pointer to make it 58-33 with less than six minutes to play. The Eagles are assured of at least a tie for fourth-place in the conference, and will play Lafayette in their next two games, the latter a conference quarterfinal in Lewisburg, Pa. ^
